```css
.light-red-pink {
  background-color: #FFB6C1;
}
```

Or if you prefer to use RGB:

```css
.light-red-pink {
  background-color: rgb(255, 182, 193);
}
```

If this color doesn't match your needs, you can adjust the values to find the exact shade you're looking for. For example, to make it lighter or darker, or to adjust the red and blue values to get the perfect shade of light red-pink you're envisioning. Tools like color pickers and online color palette generators can help you find the exact CSS code for the color you have in mind.

